      "content": "but that's just playing both sides. if u had to actually pick a side, which one is the \"right\" one? like is it fundamentally more \"correct\" to be fiscally disciplined and keep the debt low, or is it more \"right\" to prioritize people's immediate needs regardless of the deficit? there's gotta be a baseline priority here.",
